&lt;img alt="ValeriyaSpeller" src="https://i.imgur.com/bqRl8eD.png"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</summary><content type="html">&lt;div class="admonition warning"&gt;
&lt;p class="admonition-title"&gt;Outdated code&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ValeriyaSpeller worked for me in 2017, but it looks like its code isn’t compatible with newer SublimeLinter versions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;June 6 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;1. Briefly&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Russian-language spellchecker for Sublime Text.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;2. Demonstration&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="Sublime Text Window" src="https://i.imgur.com/bqRl8eD.png"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="Error report" src="https://i.imgur.com/5x542fy.png"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;3. Motivation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;i need extra spellchecker for Russian-language texts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;4. Testing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tested on:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Windows 10 Enterprise LTSB 64-bit EN,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sublime Text Build 3126,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Node.js v7.8.0,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;yaspeller 3.1.0,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;literature works of Chekhov, Dostoyevsky, Leonid Andreyev and Oliver Sacks (in Russian translation) — favorite Valeria writers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must be works in macOS and *nix operating systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;5. Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install &lt;a href="https://nodejs.org/en/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Node.js&lt;/a&gt;, if no. For Windows users I recommend &lt;a href="https://lifehacker.ru/2015/01/08/chocolatey/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;install Chocolatey&lt;/a&gt; → install Node.js by &lt;a href="https://chocolatey.org/packages/nodejs" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;command&lt;/a&gt; &lt;code class="SashaCodeInline"&gt;choco install nodejs -y&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install &lt;a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/yaspeller" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;yaspeller&lt;/a&gt; — &lt;code class="SashaCodeInline"&gt;npm install yaspeller -g&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install &lt;a href="https://packagecontrol.io/packages/SublimeLinter" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;SublimeLinter&lt;/a&gt; framework &lt;a href="https://docs.cs.cf.ac.uk/notes/sublime-text-packages/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;via Package Control&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.macdrifter.com/2012/08/install-sublime-packages-from-github.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Install&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://github.com/Kristinita/SublimeLinter-contrib-ValeriyaSpeller" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;ValeriyaSpeller&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;6. Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;6.1. Required&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ValeriyaSpeller highlight/output typos in next types of files:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Markdown,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HTML,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;LaTeX,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comments in any language.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: ValeryaLinter must work in most cases. If no, &lt;a href="https://www.sublimetext.com/docs/3/syntax.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;your syntax&lt;/a&gt; don’t have any of these &lt;a href="https://www.sublimetext.com/docs/3/scope_naming.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;scopes&lt;/a&gt; — &lt;code class="SashaCodeInline"&gt;text.html.markdown&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code class="SashaCodeInline"&gt;text.plain&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code class="SashaCodeInline"&gt;text.tex.latex&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code class="SashaCodeInline"&gt;comment&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After installation open any of these files → and see:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ValeriyaSpeller marks in &lt;a href="http://ru.stackoverflow.com/q/637536/199934" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;gutter&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ValeriyaSpeller suggests in &lt;a href="https://www.google.ru/search?q=status+bar&amp;amp;newwindow=1&amp;amp;source=lnms&amp;amp;tbm=isch&amp;amp;sa=X&amp;amp;ved=0ahUKEwi-j9WygojTAhVGiSwKHfRhATYQ_AUIBigB&amp;amp;biw=1173&amp;amp;bih=729" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;status bar&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;6.2. Optional&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may select different &lt;a href="http://www.sublimelinter.com/en/latest/lint_modes.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank"&gt;SublimeLinter modes&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also you open linting file → &lt;kbd&gt;Ctrl+Shift+P&lt;/kbd&gt; (&lt;kbd&gt;⌘⇧p&lt;/kbd&gt; for Mac) → &lt;code class="SashaCodeInline"&gt;SublimeLinter: Report (Open Files)&lt;/code&gt; → and see all linting errors and warnings of all your enabled SublimeLinter linters for all  opened files.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;6.3. Detail output&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can to give detailed output, example:&lt;/p&gt;
